igious naturalism is not currently more of a movement, but nevertheless predicts that it will become the prevailing religious sensibility.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aNaturalismxReligious aspects. 0aNaturexReligious aspects. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Atheism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438438016423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438438016/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles